<p>"The fellow's name is Cecil Harlow," Lestrade explained, "a self-proclaimed 'Ectoplasmic Engineer'. His audiences are drawn from all walks of life – from grieving parents to curious scientists, even respected members of the spiritualist community. He claims that his machine harnesses ethereal energies to open a conduit to the afterlife."</p>
